news.title: Russia says any meeting of leaders on Ukraine must be thoroughly prepared as it launches largest attack
Man who was allegedly pushed by garda dies in hospital
news.summary: A 51-year-old man who suffered critical head injuries after being allegedly pushed by a garda has died in hospital.

news.title: Holly Baxter: Donald Trump’s meeting with Volodymyr Zelensky was even worse than their last Oval Office encounter
news.summary: After Friday’s red carpet love-in with Russian leader Vladimir Putin, US president Donald Trump sat down with Ukraine’s Volodymyr Zelensky yesterday at the Oval Office to talk peace and the world hoped it would go better than the last White House meeting between the US and Ukraine.

news.title: Five things we learnt this morning as the presidential race heats up
news.summary: As a Fine Gael internal battle gets underway, other parties and candidates are under pressure.

news.title: Seán Kelly and Heather Humphreys confirm battle for Fine Gael nomination to run for Áras
news.summary: Former Minister Heather Humphreys and Fine Gael MEP Seán Kelly have both announced their intentions to seek the Fine Gael nomination to run for president.

news.title: Rose of Tralee review: Dog yoga and the Jumbo Breakfast Roll – did what I’ve been watching really happen, or am I hallucinating?
news.summary: It’s around the two-hour mark on night one of  The Rose of Tralee  (RTÉ One, Monday, August 18) that the existential mini-crisis hits: did what I’ve been watching really happen, or did I just imagine all of it?

news.title: Woman seriously injured in Dublin cliff fall
news.summary: A woman who was rescued after falling 12 metres from a cliff in south Dublin was rushed to hospital with serious injuries in an emergency multi-agency operation last night.

news.title: Gardaí feared Ian Bailey tried to  contaminate Sophie Toscan du Plantier murder scene with DNA traces
news.summary: As potentially dramatic DNA results are awaited from new vacuum tests on the rock and breeze block that were used to kill Sophie Toscan du Plantier, it can be revealed there was garda anxiety over Ian Bailey visiting the crime scene.

news.title: David Clifford interview: ‘You understand how hard All-Irelands are to win, so you cherish the ones we’ve won’
news.summary: David Clifford has always played his competitive football – whether it’s in Austin Stack Park, Páirc Uí Chaoimh or Croke Park – like he’s kicking about in the family garden; pulling catches out of the Fossa sky, selling dummies to invisible defenders, nonchalantly kicking points over the clothesline.

news.title: Former bank employee due in court over alleged fraud offence charges
news.summary: A former bank employee is due before court later to be charged with multiple alleged fraud offences linked to his time working with the bank.
